OL,3,CEconomy is improving but people still
OL,4,Cfeel poorer - so why call an election
OL,5,Cnow?
OL,7,FThe Bank of England expects inflation
OL,8,Fto rise again by the end of the year
OL,9,Fand the lived experience of many
OL,10,Fvoters is that everything is more
OL,11,Fexpensive because prices are
OL,12,Fstabilising at a much higher level
OL,13,Fthan three years ago.
OL,15,FThe Bank also forecasts unemployment
OL,16,Fwill rise further in the coming months
OL,17,Fand although interest rates are
OL,18,Fexpected to fall they are unlikely to
OL,19,Fdo so in a way that will leave
OL,20,Fmortgages holders feeling materially
OL,21,Fbetter off.
